			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Not sure when this started to flake out, but it only took me two tries to hit the flake (since the test itself does many repetitions as well). Put the attached script in the native_client directory, and run it to repro.

Alternatively, run the test with a higher &amp;quot;-r&amp;quot; option like 10000 (to repeat 10000 times):

/usr/bin/python tools/command_tester.py --name nacl_newlib.run_sigpipe_test --report scons-out/opt-linux-arm/test_results/sigpipe_test.out --time_warning 2 --time_error 20 --perf_env_description arm_pnacl_newlib_static_irt --subarch 32 --arch arm toolchain/linux_arm-trusted/run_under_qemu_arm scons-out/opt-linux-arm/obj/src/shared/imc/sigpipe_test -r 10000

The test is multi-threaded, so the log you see when it fails can vary wildly.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-15T19:05:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-12-15T22:39:26.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>Arm sigpipe src/shared/imc test (run_sigpipe_test) is flaky under qemu</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Defect</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-2</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-Linux</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-PNaCl</ns2:label><ns2:label>Arch-ARM</ns2:label><ns2:label>Mstone-X</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2494/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2494" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/2494" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>1</ns2:stars><ns2:id>2494</ns2:id></ns0:entry>